name: Adam Banton
bio:
Bike rider. Musician. Van driver. Part owner @thebikerandbaker  Support from @thespacebrace @badgerbalm @renovovita 
@tasco_mtb

social_posts.post_text: #tbt In 2015 I moved to the Denver area.  That year was a huge life learning year in many ways.  In the meantime I was stoked to ride the Arvada park often and made a lot of really great friends from Colorado.  Other notable is I have a very understanding wife that I uprooted this year as well. Thanks @jennysweettruth  thx for the pic @big_e38
S N O W D O N A from the weekend.  Took the van up and  experienced 20F nights and a wintery mix on the trails.  Wasn’t expecting any of it, excited to experience all of it.

One of the first things I got way before I got the van was a  diverse compact first aid kit made by @mymedicofficial  I’ve always had a make shift one in all my cars and believe in the value of having one.  Through the years I actually have had to get into them.  Mostly for someone else from riding.  But using it just once, is reason enough.  If your interested in getting one you can use  ADAMBANTON15 to save some cash.  They are worth it.  Have a safe and healthy holiday everyone! #mymedicambassador #experienceelevatedfirstaid

Back from Deep in the Virginia mountains.  This time last year my parents were fighting Covid in the hospital. It got scary. So being home felt extra good this year. No bike and temps in the teens.  Here’s  Random photos for very random holiday adventures. It’s a new year and I had a good one. Ending it using my OG Pac-man pillow case, fake snowboarding, beard grooming tips from my brother, frozen water fall hikes and seeing old stuff in the woods.  Happy New year you guys, let’s be the best we can in 2023 on and off bikes!

Deep into southern Arizona off a long few roads is where we slept last night.  Nobody around and the stars were bright until clouds rolled in. Any good trails in Cochise country area? Floating around in this zone.
This little hit is always a highlight for me.  If I try and pop the  mellow lip I dead sale it.  Float off and it’s perfect.  Train bell effect is a bonus!

I didn’t know I needed a bread knife until I got a bread knife.  @jennysweettruth has been making sour dough 3 years strong.  I seriously eat a slice almost every night w/olive oil .  Now I’m feeling like bready Kruger using this 8” slice slayer masterpiece.  @skallywagtactical  you guys area awesome! So far I still have 10 fingers…
Sedona is like one big skatepark that allows bikes.  I’m  a sucker for some baby rock rolls with an extra brake check at the end.

Mother Nature doesn’t ask questions.  She’s in charge.  But we all made the best of it and had fun at @sedonamtbfestival.  Saw old friends ,made new ones and hiked some trails instead of riding them. Made a snowdona ball and enjoyed good coffee in the van with @jennysweettruth.  I was paranoid about getting us stuck in the muddy lot we camped in. Luckily most of it was firm.  12” of snow in Sedona is an amazing sight to take in.  Looking forward to next years event!

This has been a LONG TIME coming and I’m super stoked to talk about my granola company @thebikerandbaker new flavor! 

FINALLY!! The Horizon is available!!

It’s a chai, blueberry and Arizona pecan organic GF granola.  I make our chai mix and it’s heavy on ginger.  It stays true to our core values of anything we will ever produce. Organic, anti-inflammatory and loaded with nourishment. 

We have included another Arizona grown ingredient.  And it’s a true powerhouse.  Local and fresh pecans!  I drove 3 hrs to visit the family farm to meet them and see their organic practices. 

Our 3 flavors are meant for a quick healthy snack or meal that tastes amazing with huge benefits.  So you can basically keep riding more and recover properly. 

Visit www.thebikerandbaker.com to order and learn more! 

Thank you all for the support. It’s been a journey. 

Supporting rider owned companies matters. 

If your a retail shop that’s interested.  Let’s talk!

We may have ran out of water but spend half the day enjoying tons of features on the new boulder dash trail at hawes. All fun stuff and a few reminded me of some Bmx/snowboard park features.  Seems to be mostly tucked in the middle of mountains so bring extra water, tools, food.  Refreshing to have stuff to session! Massive hard work from volunteers and @hawestrailalliance. Bravo guys!  Thx for filming @jonnysimonetti

VAN UPDATE! Between shorter trips I’ve  been slowly acquiring must have items for longer adventures. Originally I was going to wall mount a monitor for @jennysweettruth to have a @lucid.together mobile office.  Then I found this rad clip on screen from Teamgee.  Goes landscape or vertical and has speakers too.  Perfect for her Air Pro. Stoked we can keep a clean look inside the van now. Here’s a code if you want to grab one! 10DXVZHB.  Head here-https://www.amazon.com/promocode/A3HOZ20YHEV5YD

Yesterdays sunset session was a fun mix.  Met up with @lance_jl  and pedaled straight up a mountain. Some flow trails and a taste of a new jump line. Dare I say it’s smooth enough for BMX, definitely for @fingerscrossedbmx. Worth the hour drive every time.  Thanks  @hawestrailalliance  and crew for creating another gem.  Thx for the pic Lance.

We did an Arizona weekend as you could get.  Bikes, off-roading, snakes, cool desert mornings and sunsets. All while staying local.  This is the first time pushing off road limits on the van. Stoked the Bikes were rock solid with @unakagearco forrk mounts! A bit stressful running stock tires on rocky and super bermy turns. 45 mins to drive 2 miles. Hahah. Talked with 2 other over landers as they were staring at our big stock 170  RWD. Giving us props but also info on sketchy stuff ahead.  New camping spots are always a gamble.  But this was a Great weekend!

I can’t think of any other person in BMX doing more for zero personal gain than Karl at @nowearbmx.  Besides providing a FREE indoor skatepark on his own land  at the compound. Now he is throwing a contest with a $5,000 pro purse + tons of other prizes. AND a girls class.  I sent out some bags of @thebikerandbaker  he’s giving out as  well. Make it to this if you can! Thanks for being an amazing example to me and the rest of BMX Karl.

Big bikes with BMX friends are the best. Deep into the mountains with Long Shuttle runs on sketchy forest roads.  Almost 3k desent and @jennysweettruth kept it rubber side down. There were some dirt surfing loose and steep sections. All this And getting the van on 3 wheels for a second suns up the weekend. Super fun time in the Mazatals!

Summer is almost here and I am very stoked about this portable awning.  Simple, quick set up, temporary  and only 8lbs.  Checks off all the boxes for me.  Shade is crucial in the desert.  These work with vans, cars, trucks etc.  Wish I knew about this when I had the Subie/RTT set up. @moon_fabrications great design on this thing!

It’s taking a long time to be interested in a gravel bike.  But I’m stoked on this. I added @teravail Rutland tires and @blackburndesign lights and bottle cage for the summer.  Also Love that bag under the top tube… stocked with @thebikerandbaker granola of course. It’s simple and gets the job done.  My first BMX was a @mongoosebikes and I’m staying true for the drop bar bikes.
Sold my daily driver for a van.  Surprised myself making such a radical decision. I’m either home a lot or gone a lot.  Summer plans have begun and I’m bringing both bikes.  Location suggestions?
A week ago I got a some fun shuttle runs.  Flow, jibs, rocks and a few short steeps.  I never thought the simple things could be so fun.

My Monday was spent about 3 hrs under ground in a long tube like cave with my brother and @jennysweettruth. Highlights were not slipping on mini glaciers at entrance, Sharing long exposure skills to Andy who is super stoked on it now and hearing 2 different solo hikers talking to them selves. I swear… they let anyone in caves these days.

Made a quick field trip over to @rigidindustries today and met some fantastic people. They got me sorted so night driving will be way safer and more fun in the van.  When @jimbeaver15 says their the best, well I believe it! Will be sharing the final outcome!

#fbf This was on my backyard vert ramp. I spent so much time on this thing with friends. I find it funny there’s a big mesh of emerging BMX trends happening in one pic. Haro Master w/Bash, Open face with a jofa, Airwalk720 shoes, gold Shimanos (yes they are gold) 1-piece cranks, tie dye shirt. 

Also, I’m right foot forward and turning left here. 15 years later I decided to ride left foot forward and turn right. Don't ask..

Big thanks to @ltseligman for the time capsule pic.

This week is ending much better than it started.  We had our Go bags and @mymedic kits ready. Thankfully had the van to sleep in at a parking lot Tuesday night.  I’ll change some items in our bags and dial in a true evac plan, I did bring 2 of my 9 guitars (that’s not changing). But left everything else. I Want to thank every single firefighter in every form.  These air tanker pilots are skilled savages. Let’s all be smart this 4th if you live in the desert. This was a close call. #diamondfire  #airtanker #wildfire
A recent trip  in flagstaff.  Doing this on the big bike feels weird but familiar and surprisingly works very well.  Gives the same feels and smiles too.  #tabletoptuesday

I haven’t been this excited for #tabletoptuesday in a minute. 

1989.AFA contest Anne Arundel fairgrounds, Maryland. If I remember correctly it was freezing in here. Lots going on here. Gold Shimano pedals. Haro sport bash guard that I loved. Hammer elbow pads and dog bowl knee pads that I didn’t love. Echo open face helmet. Pacific palms gloves. Airwalk 720 high tops. I'm right pedal forward here, I’m now left pedal. Pinch zoom to the guy on the back quarter that's Jeremy Alder inventor of the bars-pin air, with a coaster brake of course. Pic by Bmx’s unofficial era archivist @mavrocam thanks Dave

Funny story: This past weekend was about Mountains and a decent size ride in cooler weather.  AND We accidentally found a secret rave happening near our camp spot. After the 20th car passed us down a off shoot road, I talked to one.  We got invited to dance all night to the 24 Dj’s. I declined and  packed up the van and moved 6 miles.  Passing glow sticks in bushes as markers on our exit. I still slept to faint drum and bass all night.  But was greeted by a majestic animal known as a cow in the A.M.  We also made good coffee that was needed.  Finding solitude  can be hard sometimes.  #hokkaidotigerclub
The edge on the top of this berm was so crisp.  I had to Canadian nose pick it.  Overcast skies and some good hardcore made my soul breathe happiness during this sesh.
Recent Front wheel moves at my favorite new skatepark.  This place is so fun!  Thx for filming @g1nja_ninja
Just got back from a week in the van.  Stayed local ish in Sedona and Flagstaff.  Dodged some monsoon rains everyday. Chilly mornings and lots of riding. Big squishy bikes are fun!

Getting this thing to make sense has been fun and challenging. This dish is tighter than it always looks but getting used to it and the ideas are flowing.  I was winging it on getting out once I got in.  It slides good with plastic pegs though.  Good session!

Time for the Sprinter vans first oil change!  Everything with the  van is a bit different from a car. So I ordered a oil change kit from www.blauparts .com and everything went smooth.  It was even kinda satisfying. You can Use code ADAMBANTON10  to save some money when ordering from them!

I can be very sarcastic and love a good play on words, mix in never have been scared to do things my way…. and I find myself a perfect fit with @tasco_mtb  Read on…

True freedom is found living your life behind bars.  It’s a freedom from a mundane, confined, predictable lifestyle.  The moment you are behind the bars, and you grab onto them, you find the adrenaline immediately starts pumping through your veins and the world as you knew it will never look the same. 

I’m super stoked to be a part of the TASCO Chain Gang, a special crew of riders dedicated to living life on their terms.  We have one thing in common – we have unapologetically chosen to live our life behind bars.  Living life behind bars typically has a bad connotation, but not to this crew – we love it and wouldn’t trade it for anything.  Click the link in my bio to learn more about what got me into a life behind bars!

#tascostoke #tascobehindbars
The stoke is very high when it’s over cast and I know cooler temps are coming!  Finding the box jump line in this pump track maze.  Thx for the pic @g1nja_ninja
I love this trick. Kinda a secret front brake move. Or forward slider grind?  I just reference to  it as the turn bar feeble.  This ledge is near perfect and buttered too.

Every car I’ve ever owned I was slightly obsessed on aftermarket floor mats. The van is no exception and the stoke was real when my @smartlinerusa  floorliners showed up right before a flagstaff/Sedona trip in the van.  Bonus-I got to show off all my favorite socks making this vid!

I keep certain parts of my life off social media. So this is a rare but worthy post. 

Over the weekend @jennysweettruth  and I celebrated 7 years of commitment together of being married(15yrs together). 

All her friends including her family and even Jennifer told me she would never get married  She asked me one time why I wanted to marry her, with a quick reaction I said “because you deserve more than a boyfriend”  Every year that’s gone by I find  more answers to  that question. 

Thanks for accepting me for me whole heartedly Jennifer.  I love you and happy anniversary. It seems fitting to pick the song I wrote for Jennifer in 2014 in this post. ❤️ 

Big thanks for capturing genuine gazing from @justinkosman
Driving through a prescription burn to get down  in a cave to  play with light painting. A crazy experience.  Then back to the norm of Van camping and riding bikes

Something I had wanted for some time now was a good cover for the van. @sealskincovers had what I needed and now  this beast can be protected from all the Arizona elements year round. Get a cover for your vehicle use my code Adam15 and save some cash(15%off) #sealskincovers  That sweet wolf shirt is not included
This is the first time hitting a dirt quarter on 29” wheels.  Recalibrated my head and tables were feeling good.  Great crew out there.  Papago jumps are running strong.  Thx for the pic @g1nja_ninja

First run of the day I made a last minute  decision to gap something and it landed me directly on the frames  bottom bracket area .  Was a Nasty sound on impact.  My bash guard got bent but took most of the blow.  I zip tied everything together and kept riding. Fun day riding the Hawes area with a solid crew.  Winter in the desert is so good!

I love bike shops.  I still remember the first “real” shop I went to ages ago in Virginia.  I recently got to visit @gearupvelo in the Cleveland area who carries @thebikerandbaker granola, my granola company.
 
I’ve known Brian@wookie_b  from the OG Chenga crew for a long time.  And it means a lot to have him carrier our product 

If you’re in the Cleveland area and want to buy our granola swing by and stock up! Thanks Brian and all who support rider owned brands.

New year New unintentional frame. 

Breaking carbon frames isn’t that  fun.  But having friends like @big_e38  to  do the frame swap makes it much better.  Thanks for the pro turn around time and set up Erik! 

 Is this really my 3rd Switchblade?  When I like something I stick to it I guess. Happy 2024 everyone. I wish you a healthy and successful year!
Impossible to show how this hip is on a downhill slant.  But the stoke was real riding this feature yesterday with @damangler Many jibs happened!  Good  ride.

Bike rider. Musician. Van driver. Part owner @thebikerandbaker  Support from @thespacebrace @badgerbalm @renovovita
